Constructor Detail

TabContentProxyImpl

public TabContentProxyImpl()
Creates a Proxy for a Presenter that is meant to be contained within at TabContainerPresenter. As such, these proxy hold a string that can be displayed on the tab.

Method Detail

getTargetHistoryToken

public String getTargetHistoryToken()
Description copied from interface: TabContentProxy
Gets the history token that should be accessed when the tab is clicked. In the fairly typical scenario where a tab directly contains a place, this should return the name token of that place. In the case of tabs that contain non-leaf presenters (for example, other tabs), this should return the name token of a leaf-level presenter.

Specified by:

bind

@Inject
protected void bind(ProxyFailureHandler failureHandler,
                           EventBus eventBus)
Description copied from class: ProxyImpl
Injects the various resources and performs other bindings.

Never call directly, it should only be called by GIN. Method injection is used instead of constructor injection, because the latter doesn't work well with GWT generators.
